<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-01-05T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-01-05T06:00:00-05:00" n="11" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d11">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">794.94/5687: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan (<persName type="from">Grew</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-01-05T20:00:00+09:00">January 5, 1933—8
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received January 5—9:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>6. The Minister for Foreign Affairs told me today that instructions have
                            been sent to the Japanese military authorities in Manchuria to localize
                            the Shanhaikwan affair unless Chinese provocation renders further
                            measures necessary.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Peiping.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>